name: definition_d1_heat_equation
description: The **heat equation** describes temperature evolution:

$$\frac{\partial T}{\partial t}(\mathbf{x}, t) = \alpha \nabla^2 T(\mathbf{x}, t)$$

Where $\alpha > 0$ is thermal diffusivity.
tags: concept, 11-thermal-simulation

---
pattern: "definition $params"
expand: |
    MOVI R0, 0
    HALT
result: R0
name: definition_d2_discrete_heat_equation
description: For n agents at positions $\{\mathbf{x}_i\}$:

$$\frac{d T_i}{d t} = \alpha \sum_{j \neq i} K_{ij}(T_j - T_i)$$

Where $K_{ij}$ is the thermal coupling coefficient.
tags: concept, 11-thermal-simulation

---
pattern: "definition $params"
expand: |
    MOVI R0, 0
    HALT
result: R0
name: definition_d3_thermal_kernel
description: The **thermal kernel** determines coupling strength:

$$K_{ij} = \frac{1}{|\mathbf{x}_i - \mathbf{x}_j|^2 + \epsilon^2}$$

Where $\epsilon$ prevents singularity at zero distance.
tags: concept, 11-thermal-simulation

